vulnerability.name: USN-5651-1
vulnerability.description: Lahav Schlesinger discovered that strongSwan incorrectly handled certain OCSP URIs and and CRL distribution points (CDP) in certificates. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to initiate IKE_SAs and send crafted certificates that contain URIs pointing to servers under their control, which can lead to a denial-of-service attack.

statements.status_notes: strongSwan could be made do denial of service if it received a specially crafted certificate.
